no.uio.studentweb.sword
Class Depositor

java.lang.Object
  no.uio.studentweb.sword.Depositor

public class Depositor
extends java.lang.Object

Class to handle the deposit operations required between StudentWeb and the repository using SWORDv2. This is effectively a thin wrapper around the SWORDv2 client library

setGradeWithPermanentEmbargo

public SwordResponse setGradeWithPermanentEmbargo(java.lang.String editUri,
                                                  AuthCredentials auth,
                                                  java.lang.String grade)
                                           throws SWORDClientException,
                                                  SWORDError
Set an item's grade and permanently embargo it. This is equivalent to calling setGrade(java.lang.String, AuthCredentials, java.lang.String, java.util.Date, java.lang.String) with a an embargo of Constants.EMBARGO_PERMANENT

Parameters:
editUri - The SWORDv2 Edit-URI of the item, as obtained from the DepositReceipt after the original deposit
auth - The SWORDv2 authentication credentials
grade - The grade to set, should be one of Constants.PASS or Constants.FAIL
Returns:
A DepositReceipt object
Throws:
SWORDClientException
SWORDError
